At @ClusterOne_ we still see an #AI infrastructure bottleneck at most companies. Computing has become a commodity but managing it efficiently is a challenge. When ML engineers are so hard to find - making sure their time is not spent on DevOps is critical.
Exoskeletons are not off-topic! These are great innovations for this purpose.

There’s a number that will help agriculture to help feed the world while damaging it less, such as drones that plant seeds and micro spray pesticides on only the plants that need it through detection by AI & computer vision
Or the missing socks from the dryer. That robot would be my personal hero.
I’m waiting for the one that finds the matching Tupperware lid, such a frustrating process

Other than that - I wonder if a robot will carry your groceries from your car to your fridge. More realistically robots will change our environment fundamentally. Maybe there'll be no fridges anymore. Or no stores.

The intersection of #robots + #humans is amazing. @ExoWandercraft for example is developing exoskeletons for spinal cord injury patients. They may WALK again. Slightly off topic - couldn't help but give a shout out to these guys. http://www. wandercraft.eu/en/ . #FrenchTech
